{"key":"processedPost-11737644","value":{"id":11737644,"first":11735364,"last":11741545,"when":1262120206,"utime":"12/29/09 10:56 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>Fahkface said:</b><br />If you see, that it's drying out, mist it! If it keeps losing moisture, tape some holes until it's OK.<br /></blockquote><br /><br />Actually, it's better to mist more rather than close holes.&nbsp; Fresh air is the number ONE pinning trigger because it causes evaporation from the substrate.&nbsp; If the substrate is losing moisture, the mycelium will produce fruit bodies as a survival mechanism.&nbsp; Mist to replace the lost moisture, but don't try to restrict it.<br />RR","title":"Re: Pressure"}}